Allow a swap-backed Cangjie heap larger than physical RAM (bootstrap only).

The O1-seed stage1 compiling the chir package needs a ~20GB heap (usedObj
9.4GB at 38% region fragmentation); the 16GB runner carries it on swap, but
InitHeapSize rejects any cjHeapSize above g_sysmemSize and silently falls
back to the tiny default. Raise the cap to 2x RAM for the source-build SDK.

--- a/runtime/src/CjScheduler.cpp
+++ b/runtime/src/CjScheduler.cpp
@@ -100,7 +100,8 @@
     // 4UL * KB: The minimum heap size, measured in KB, the value is 4MB.
     size_t minSize = 4UL * KB;
 #endif
-    size_t maxSize = g_sysmemSize / KB;
+    // cjcj srcbuild: permit swap-backed heaps up to twice physical memory.
+    size_t maxSize = (g_sysmemSize * 2) / KB;
     if (size >= minSize && size <= maxSize) {
         return size;
     } else {
